definitions: denoting or relating to a person whose sense of personal identity and gender does not correspond with their birth sex

examples.text: the film plays into negative stereotypes about trans people
Perry, who is trans, fought against her high school for her right to use the girls' locker room
trans rights and societal attitudes have changed

definitions: denoting or relating to a molecular structure in which two particular atoms or groups lie on opposite sides of a given plane in the molecule, in particular denoting an isomer in which substituents at opposite ends of a carbon–carbon double bond are also on opposite sides of the bond
shortDefinitions: denoting or relating to molecular structure
